    <div class="container">
        <div class="row justify-content-center">
            <div class="col-md-12 col-lg-9"><br><br><h5> This article is reformatted from originally published at <a href="https://medium.com/the-wisest-friends/the-paradox-that-keeps-mathematicians-up-at-night-90526ce34f66"><strong>TDS(Towards Data Science)</strong></a></h5></br><h5> <a href="https://medium.com/@samratduttaofficial?source=post_page-----90526ce34f66--------------------------------">Author : Samrat Dutta</a> </h5></div></div></div></section><section data-bs-version="5.1" class="content4 cid-tt5SM2WLsM" id="content4-2" style="padding-top:0px; padding-bottom:0px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);">
            <div class="container">
                <div class="row justify-content-center">
                    <div class="title col-md-12 col-lg-9">
                        <h3 class="mbr-section-title mbr-fonts-style mb-4 display-2">
                            <strong>The Paradox That Keeps Mathematicians up All Night</h3></div></div></div></section><section data-bs-version="5.1" class="content5 cid-tt5UseJ9wk" id="content5-4" style="padding-top:0px; padding-bottom:0px;background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);">
    <div class="container">
        <div class="row justify-content-center">
            <div class="col-md-12 col-lg-9"><h4 class="mbr-section-subtitle mbr-fonts-style mb-4 display-5 text-muted">What we know about mathematical proofs was changed by Gödel’s Incompleteness Theorem.</h4></div></div></div></section><section data-bs-version="5.1" class="image3 cid-tt612oXwA9" id="image3-5" style="padding-top:0px; padding-bottom:0px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);">
